 data-testid=3D"articleSectionText" class=3D"css-h9evcv e1taq3sq1"><div cla=
ss=3D"ed4x0bn0 css-48o5u4 e1m4c3o81"><div class=3D"textBlock"><p>A <strong>=
central angle</strong> is an angle with a vertex at the center of a circle =
whose arms extend to the circumference. You can imagine the central angle b=
eing at the tip of a pizza slice in a large circular pizza.</p>
<p>You can find the central angle of a circle using the formula:</p>
<p><code>=CE=B8 =3D L / r</code></p>
<p>where <code>=CE=B8</code> is the central angle in radians, <code>L</code=
> is the arc length, and <code>r</code> is the radius.</p></div></div></div=
></section><section data-testid=3D"articleSection-1" data-cwv-id=3D"calcula=
