lass=3D"ed4x0bn0 css-48o5u4 e1m4c3o81"><div class=3D"textBlock"><p>The simp=
licity of the central angle formula originates from the definition of a rad=
ian. A <strong>radian</strong> is a unit of angular size, where 1 radian is=
 defined as a central angle (<code>=CE=B8</code>) whose arc length is equal=
 to the radius (<code>L =3D r</code>).</p></div></div></div></section><sect=
ion data-testid=3D"articleSection-2" data-cwv-id=3D"calculator-article-sect=
