class=3D"css-h9evcv e1taq3sq1"><div class=3D"ed4x0bn0 css-48o5u4 e1m4c3o81"=
><div class=3D"textBlock"><p>To find the central angle of a circle, use the=
 formula:</p>
<p><code>=CE=B8 =3D L / r</code></p>
<p>where:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>=CE=B8</code> =E2=80=94 Central angle in radians;</li>
<li><code>L</code> =E2=80=94 Arc length; and</li>
<li><code>r</code> =E2=80=94 Radius of the circle.</li>
</ul></div><div class=3D"textBlock"><p>To find the central angle of a circl=
e, you need to calculate the <strong>ratio of arc length to the radius of a=
 circle</strong>.</p>
<p>You can imagine the central angle being at the tip of a pizza slice in a=
 large circular pizza.</p></div></div></div><h3 data-testid=3D"How do I fin=
d radius with arc length and central angle?" class=3D"css-1ugw61y">How do I=
